# security.yaml — PROVISIONING TEMPLATE (inactive).
#
# This .example file is NOT read by Grav. The real security.yaml is gitignored
# (WI-3): it carries the salt that feeds Grav's nonce generation and
# remember-me token signing — an authentication secret that must never be
# committed.
#
# YOU NORMALLY DO NOT NEED TO CREATE security.yaml BY HAND. When the file is
# absent, Grav regenerates it with a fresh per-instance salt on the first
# request. A clean checkout + `make start` just works.
#
# To pin a value (e.g. to keep remember-me cookies stable across a recreate),
# copy this file to security.yaml and replace the placeholder with a random
# string, for example:  openssl rand -base64 24
#
# ROTATION: the repo previously tracked a real salt (Wbd0yZKOPckagC). Rotate it
# on every tier that used it — see README "Authentication secrets" (WI-3).
salt: REPLACE_WITH_A_FRESH_RANDOM_SALT
